at Hughes Tools.


31
00:02:59.766 --> 00:03:02.517
Someone to oversee
the financial aspects of the business.


32
00:03:02.685 --> 00:03:05.437
I'm looking for somebody to run it
and do a good job.


33
00:03:05.605 --> 00:03:07.898
There's only one thing
you've gotta know.


34
00:03:08.066 --> 00:03:10.901
My folks, they're gone now.
So it's my money.


35
00:03:11.069 --> 00:03:14.780
What I do with that money may seem crazy
to those sons of bitches in Houston.


36
00:03:14.947 --> 00:03:18.533
I'm sure it does, but it all makes
good sense to me. You got that?


37
00:03:18.701 --> 00:03:20.494
- Got it.
- Good.


38
00:03:20.661 --> 00:03:23.789
Now, you made, what,
$5200 a year at your last job?


39
00:03:23.956 --> 00:03:27.834
- I'll pay you $10,000.
- I guess I'll be working twice as hard.


40
00:03:28.002 --> 00:03:31.588
You'll be working four times as hard.
I just got you at half price.


41
00:03:31.756 --> 00:03:33.256
- Welcome aboard.
- Thank you.


42
00:03:33.424 --> 00:03:35.592
You're my voice now.
Make them understand that.


43
00:03:35.760 --> 00:03:39.930
Some of those folks still call me Junior.
You tell them it's "Mr. Hughes" now.


44
00:03:40.098 --> 00:03:42.182
You bet.
So when do we go to Houston?


45
00:03:42.350 --> 00:03:45.644
