284
00:19:41.808 --> 00:19:45.102
I'm a businessman, Howard.
And so are you.


285
00:19:45.270 --> 00:19:47.063
Now, look.

286
00:19:47.230 --> 00:19:48.689
This has been a great ride.

287
00:19:48.857 --> 00:19:50.775
We've had a hell
of a lot of fun.

288
00:19:51.193 --> 00:19:54.862
But you're losing
$25,000 a day doing this.


289
00:19:55.155 --> 00:19:57.073
Every day.

290
00:20:02.621 --> 00:20:05.456
So, what are my options?

291
00:20:07.042 --> 00:20:09.794
Well, this time I don't know
that you have any.


292
00:20:09.961 --> 00:20:12.380
I'm afraid you gotta close it down.

293
00:20:13.131 --> 00:20:14.757
Dig your way out.

294
00:20:21.431 --> 00:20:23.432
I'm sorry, Howard.

295
00:20:23.975 --> 00:20:25.810
I truly am.

296
00:20:33.151 --> 00:20:34.777
Reel 10, Mr. Hughes.

297
00:20:40.826 --> 00:20:42.827
Mortgage Tool Co.

298
00:20:43.745 --> 00:20:48.833
- Every asset. You heard me.
- If you do that, you could lose everything.


299
00:20:49.000 --> 00:20:50.584
Well, I won't.

300
00:20:53.713 --> 00:20:55.172
I won't.

301
00:20:56.675 --> 00:20:58.467
All right.

302
00:20:59.678 --> 00:21:01.303
I'll get into it.

303
00:21:02.681 --> 00:21:04.223
Thanks, Noah.

304
00:21:39.342 --> 00:21:43.053
More than half a million souls lining
the curb of Hollywood Boulevard.


305
00:21:43.221 --> 00:21:44.889
Look at the automobiles!

306
00:21:45.056 --> 00:21:48.893
There are 45,000 cars here,
making it the greatest traffic jam ever seen.


307
00:21:49.060 --> 00:21:51.479
Howard Hughes must have
a lump in his throat.


308
00:21:51.646 --> 00:21:55.733
Six months after the stock market crashes
and after three pilots' deaths ...


309
00:21:55.901 --> 00:21:58.903
... he's finally unveiling his
$4 million baby doll.


310
00:21:59.070 --> 00:22:03.365
It's the most expensive movie ever made.
Nothing five-and-dime for our Mr. Hughes.


311
00:22:03.533 --> 00:22:06.827
Nothing like tonight has ever been
seen before, and I can say ...


312
00:22:06.995 --> 00:22:08.662
... it will never be seen again.

313
00:22:08.830 --> 00:22:12.833
Five hundred thousand people are crowding
the streets to get a glimpse of the stars.


314
00:22:13.001 --> 00:22:15.711
Three companies of Marines
were called to assist ...


315
00:22:15.879 --> 00:22:19.298
... the 250 special police who are
handling this enormous crowd --


316
00:22:19.466 --> 00:22:21.008
This is an industry town.

317
00:22:21.176 --> 00:22:24.094
And nobody but nobody
makes a movie outside a studio.


318
00:22:24.262 --> 00:22:27.765
Some Hollywood insiders over
at the Brown Derby may be laughing ...


319
00:22:27.933 --> 00:22:29.391
And now, I think ...

320
00:22:29.559 --> 00:22:32.394
Yes, yes, I can see
Mr. Hughes' car arriving now.


321
00:22:32.562 --> 00:22:35.523
Mr. Hughes escorts
the lovely starlet Jean Harlow.


322
00:22:35.690 --> 00:22:39.693
He discovered her for this picture,
and we think her platinum blond locks ...


323
00:22:39.861 --> 00:22:44.114
... and hot-jazz, baby-doll style
are gonna make her a big star.


324
00:22:53.083 --> 00:22:55.376
Howard! Howard!

325
00:23:01.925 --> 00:23:03.801
Over here!

326
00:23:10.350 --> 00:23:14.603
- This way, boss. Right over there.
- Mr. Hughes, how about a word?


327
00:23:14.813 --> 00:23:17.273
Big night for you, Mr. Hughes.

328
00:23:19.192 --> 00:23:21.819
Big night for you tonight.

329
00:23:21.987 --> 00:23:24.321
Very big. Very big.

330
00:23:24.489 --> 00:23:28.200
Tell us what it was like
making this fabulous picture.


331
00:23:30.036 --> 00:23:31.829
Yes.

332
00:23:31.997 --> 00:23:33.372
Yeah.

333
00:23:33.540 --> 00:23:36.166
So 4 million clams
from your own pocket.


334
00:23:36.334 --> 00:23:38.002
Nervous how the flick will fly?

335
00:23:41.548 --> 00:23:44.842
Big night. You enjoy the show.

336
00:23:45.343 --> 00:23:50.723
Yes, well, let me present the feminine
star of this spectacle, Hell's Angels ...


337
00:23:50.890 --> 00:23:53.517
... Miss Jean Harlow.
- Thank you.


338
00:23:53.685 --> 00:23:56.645
I would like to use this occasion
to thank Mr. Hughes ...


339
00:23:56.813 --> 00:24:00.107
... for the opportunity he gave me.
Thank you.


340
00:24:00.275 --> 00:24:03.652
Thank you!
Now I'd like to ask Roscoe Arbuckle ...


341
00:24:03.820 --> 00:24:06.780
... to introduce
his pet lion cub, Gilmore.


342
00:24:06.948 --> 00:24:09.617
What's the matter with you?
Can't remember my name?


343
00:24:09.784 --> 00:24:13.787
I'm sorry. Roscoe Turner,
and this would be Gilmore.


344
00:24:56.915 --> 00:24:58.582
It's going! It's going!

345
00:25:00.251 --> 00:25:03.671
Murder! That's what this
dirty, rotten politician war is, murder!


346
00:25:03.838 --> 00:25:05.297
You know it as well as I do.

347
00:25:43.086 --> 00:25:44.670
Stand up, slim, take a bow.

348
00:25:58.309 --> 00:26:00.519
Reel four played too long.
Too many coughs.


349
00:26:00.687 --> 00:26:04.648
Get the team out of the party and
to the office. I wanna cut a few shots.


350
00:26:04.816 --> 00:26:07.067
Oh, find Glenn.
Somebody write this down.


351
00:26:07.235 --> 00:26:08.485
Flush rivets.
Got that?


352
00:26:08.653 --> 00:26:10.320
- Flush rivets.
- Flush rivets.


353
00:26:10.488 --> 00:26:12.030
Lickety-split, boss.

354
00:26:12.282 --> 00:26:13.907
Here he is! Here he is!

355
00:26:15.994 --> 00:26:17.870
Variety says, "This one won't miss!"

356
00:26:18.037 --> 00:26:21.331
- Magnificently photographed!
- Awesome beyond description!


357
00:26:21.499 --> 00:26:25.085
The most extraordinary output
to emerge from a motion-picture studio.


358
00:26:25.253 --> 00:26:28.172
Not for a long time have I seen
anything as enthralling.


359
00:26:28.339 --> 00:26:31.383
It costs 4 million dollars
and has 4 million thrills!


360
00:26:31.551 --> 00:26:33.844
- Majestically ...
- Most epic picture of its time!


361
00:27:29.317 --> 00:27:32.277
A lighter shade. I don't want
to look like Boris Karloff.


362
00:27:32.445 --> 00:27:34.071
If you know what I mean.

363
00:27:35.990 --> 00:27:39.910
I read in the magazines
that you play golf.


364
00:27:40.078 --> 00:27:41.745
On occasion.

365
00:27:41.913 --> 00:27:44.164
Well, how about nine holes?

366
00:27:46.251 --> 00:27:48.418
Now, Mr. Hughes?

367
00:27:49.087 --> 00:27:51.839
If it would be convenient, Miss Hepburn.

368
00:28:14.404 --> 00:28:17.865
You're not extending
enough on your follow-through.


369
00:28:18.032 --> 00:28:20.951
Follow-through
is everything in golf, just like life.


370
00:28:21.119 --> 00:28:22.452
Don't you find?

371
00:28:22.620 --> 00:28:24.621
Saw your Scarface picture.

372
00:28:24.789 --> 00:28:26.123
- Violent.
- Realistic.


373
00:28:26.291 --> 00:28:28.625
Movies are movies, Howard.
Not life.


374
00:28:28.793 --> 00:28:30.460
Now the stage.

375
00:28:30.628 --> 00:28:31.879
The stage is real.

376
00:28:32.046 --> 00:28:36.049
Real flesh and blood. Human beings
right out there in front of you, buster.


377
00:28:36.217 --> 00:28:39.177
Can't look away. Can't munch popcorn.
That would be rude.


378
00:28:39.345 --> 00:28:40.637
Do you like the theater?

379
00:28:40.930 --> 00:28:43.432
- No.
- Oh, I adore the theater.


380
00:28:43.600 --> 00:28:45.767
Only alive on-stage.
I'll teach you.


381
00:28:45.935 --> 00:28:49.855
We'll see some Ibsen. If the Republicans
haven't outlawed him by now.


382
00:28:50.023 --> 00:28:53.066
You're not a Republican, are you?
How did you vote in '32?


383
00:28:53.234 --> 00:28:56.695
- Well, I didn't.
- You must! It's your sacred franchise.


384
00:29:00.575 --> 00:29:03.327
Heard you were wooing Ginger Rogers.
What about that?


385
00:29:03.494 --> 00:29:05.829
She's just a friend.

386
00:29:05.997 --> 00:29:07.706
Men can't be friends with women.

387
00:29:07.874 --> 00:29:09.958
They must possess them
or leave them be.


388
00:29:10.126 --> 00:29:13.253
It's a primitive urge from caveman days.
It's all in Darwin.


389
00:29:13.421 --> 00:29:18.759
Hunt the flesh, kill the flesh, eat the flesh.
That's the male sex all over.


390
00:29:19.427 --> 00:29:20.802
Excuse me?

391
00:29:21.596 --> 00:29:24.598
Well, if you're deaf,
you must own up to it.


392
00:29:24.849 --> 00:29:26.808
Get a hearing aid.
Or see my father.


393
00:29:26.976 --> 00:29:30.646
He's a urologist, but it's all tied up
inside the body, don't you find?


394
00:29:30.980 --> 00:29:32.439
Me, I keep healthy.

395
00:29:32.607 --> 00:29:34.733
I take seven showers a day
to keep clean.


396
00:29:34.901 --> 00:29:38.236
Also because I am what's so
vulgarly referred to as "outdoorsy."


397
00:29:38.404 --> 00:29:42.407
I'm not outdoorsy.
I'm athletic. I sweat.


398
00:29:42.575 --> 00:29:45.369
There it is.
Now we both know the sordid truth.


399
00:29:45.536 --> 00:29:47.996
I sweat and you're deaf.

400
00:29:48.164 --> 00:29:51.041
Aren't we a fine pair of misfits?

401
00:29:54.587 --> 00:29:56.463
Three.

402
00:30:04.013 --> 00:30:05.847
Noble effort.

403
00:30:08.226 --> 00:30:10.894
So I suppose you're
wooing me now?


404
00:30:11.562 --> 00:30:13.563
Oh, well.

405
00:30:32.625 --> 00:30:34.126
Not enough.

406
00:30:34.711 --> 00:30:37.754
Not enough.
These rivets have to be completely flush.


407
00:30:37.922 --> 00:30:40.799
I want every screw and joint countersunk.

408
00:30:41.050 --> 00:30:43.844
I want no wind resistance
on the fuselage.


409
00:30:44.012 --> 00:30:46.304
She has got to be clean, Odie.

410
00:30:46.472 --> 00:30:48.265
- Clean. Understand?
- Okay, Howard.


411
00:30:48.433 --> 00:30:50.225
I don't know
what else to tell you.


412
00:30:51.269 --> 00:30:54.855
- What do you got for me?
- The thing is, TWA needs a new plane.


413
00:30:55.023 --> 00:30:57.649
- A modern plane.
- Oh, yeah? What kind of plane?


414
00:30:57.817 --> 00:31:00.068
Okay. The DC-3 has 21 daytime seats ...

415
00:31:00.236 --> 00:31:02.654
... and 14 overnight berths.
- Something bigger?


416
00:31:03.990 --> 00:31:06.366
Try 50 seats with
a ceiling of 12,000 feet.


417
00:31:06.534 --> 00:31:08.785
No. No, 20,000.

418
00:31:09.120 --> 00:31:11.288
Think about it.
What does 20,000 feet give you?


419
00:31:11.456 --> 00:31:14.041
- Less turbulence.
- Because it's above the weather.


420
00:31:14.208 --> 00:31:16.585
Jack, we wanna fly
above the weather.


421
00:31:16.753 --> 00:31:20.297
Only 1 percent of the American population
has set foot on an airliner.


422
00:31:20.465 --> 00:31:23.258
Why? Because they're scared to death.
They should be.


423
00:31:23.426 --> 00:31:26.011
I mean, 7000 feet is bumpy as shit.
You know that.


424
00:31:26.179 --> 00:31:28.680
We build a plane
that flies above the weather ...


425
00:31:28.848 --> 00:31:32.642
... we could get every man, woman
and child in this country to feel safe.


426
00:31:32.810 --> 00:31:37.314
An airplane with the ability to fly into
the sub-stratosphere across the country.


427
00:31:37.482 --> 00:31:39.316
Across the world.

428
00:31:39.484 --> 00:31:41.568
Now that is the future.

429
00:31:41.986 --> 00:31:43.236
- You with me?
- Yeah.


430
00:31:43.404 --> 00:31:47.324
I don't wanna get into this
if your board doesn't have the balls for it.


431
00:31:47.492 --> 00:31:49.826
- Would they support us?
- I don't know.


432
00:31:49.994 --> 00:31:52.204
- What's your financial picture?
- Not great.


433
00:31:52.371 --> 00:31:54.539
- Last year's deficit?
- 770,000.


434
00:31:54.707 --> 00:31:57.417
- What's it selling at?
- About 8 dollars a share.


435
00:31:57.585 --> 00:31:59.336
That's the lowest it's been, huh?

436
00:32:01.297 --> 00:32:02.756
I could do that.

437
00:32:02.924 --> 00:32:04.424
- Do what?
- Buy it.


438
00:32:04.592 --> 00:32:07.260
- You wanna buy the airline?
- For crying out loud ...


439
00:32:07.428 --> 00:32:11.348
... we don't want pencil pushers getting
in the way of us making our plane.


440
00:32:11.516 --> 00:32:15.352
Give me brass tacks, now. What does
controlling interest in TWA cost me?


441
00:32:16.354 --> 00:32:17.771
Call it 15 million.

442
00:32:20.191 --> 00:32:22.359
That is a chunk of change, huh?

443
00:32:25.780 --> 00:32:27.614
You call Noah Dietrich.

444
00:32:27.782 --> 00:32:29.741
You have him start buying.

445
00:32:29.909 --> 00:32:31.201
Howard, hold on.

446
00:32:31.369 --> 00:32:34.371
Are you sure?
You wanna think about it for five minutes?


447
00:32:34.539 --> 00:32:38.375
Hell, Jack, I got a tiger by the tail here.
I ain't gonna let it go.


448
00:32:47.218 --> 00:32:48.927
Good evening, Mr. Hughes.

449
00:32:49.095 --> 00:32:51.471
Welcome. Your table is ready.

450
00:32:52.640 --> 00:32:54.182
How goes the aviation?

451
00:32:54.350 --> 00:32:57.310
- Oh, just fine, Pete.
- I'm so glad.


452
00:32:59.647 --> 00:33:00.981
Good evening, Mr. Hughes.

453
00:33:01.149 --> 00:33:02.399
- Madame.
- It's "miss."


454
00:33:02.567 --> 00:33:04.985
Miss. The usual, Mr. Hughes?

455
00:33:05.153 --> 00:33:07.279
- Please.
- May I recommend for the lady ...


456
00:33:07.446 --> 00:33:10.949
... our clementine soup followed
by roast duck with currant glaze ...


457
00:33:11.117 --> 00:33:14.077
... and poached pears in rose sauce.
It's truly divine.


458
00:33:14.245 --> 00:33:15.745
Yeah. That sounds fine.

459
00:33:17.915 --> 00:33:20.667
Your kind of joint, is it?

460
00:33:21.794 --> 00:33:23.378
Wouldn't have thought.

461
00:33:23.546 --> 00:33:26.756
They're open late.
I go to a hot-dog stand on "La Cienega" too.


462
00:33:26.924 --> 00:33:29.593
- They're open till about 4.
- Are they?


463
00:33:31.596 --> 00:33:33.430
How marvelous.

464
00:33:49.280 --> 00:33:50.947
Howard! Howard!

465
00:33:51.908 --> 00:33:54.659
Hi! Son of a gun.

466
00:33:54.827 --> 00:33:58.663
Kate, this is Johnny Meyer.
I suppose you could call him my press agent.


467
00:33:58.831 --> 00:34:01.124
- Pleased to meet you. Loved Alice Adams.
- You're too kind.


468
00:34:01.292 --> 00:34:03.960
- I'm sure you know Errol, right?
- Mr. Flynn. Yes.


469
00:34:04.128 --> 00:34:09.007
Kate. Kate. Kate of the clenched-jawed
Hepburns. Enchanting as always.


470
00:34:09.175 --> 00:34:11.885
You should use Lux on your hands,
by the way. I do.


471
00:34:12.053 --> 00:34:14.221
You and Howard
ought to cook up a picture.


472
00:34:14.388 --> 00:34:16.932
Co-star with Errol.
I could sell that in spades.


473
00:34:17.099 --> 00:34:19.309
That would be marvelous. Howard?

474
00:34:19.894 --> 00:34:23.647
I think not.
Don't you read Variety, Mr. Meyer?


475
00:34:23.814 --> 00:34:27.484
Well, I'm box-office poison.
I'm on the outs, the skids, the doldrums.


476
00:34:27.652 --> 00:34:31.029
Washed-up, day-old fish
not worth the eating, so they tell me.


477
00:34:31.197 --> 00:34:35.033
Hell with them. Hell with them, my dear.
Soulless pricks to a man, right?


478
00:34:35.201 --> 00:34:39.246
Johnny tells me you're thinking about
doing a Western, of all goddamn things.


479
00:34:43.334 --> 00:34:46.086
Are you making a Western, Howard?

480
00:34:46.295 --> 00:34:49.047
Yeah. Making a Western.
I'm gonna call it The Outlaw.


481
00:34:49.215 --> 00:34:51.383
Yeah. And you know
what it's about? S-E-X.


482
00:34:51.550 --> 00:34:54.261
- It's all about S-E-X.
- It's a Western.


483
00:34:54.428 --> 00:34:57.347
You can't have fornication in a Western.
It isn't done.


484
00:34:57.515 --> 00:34:59.307
It's not real sex, it's movie sex.

485
00:34:59.475 --> 00:35:03.144
What Scarface did for the gangster picture,
The Outlaw will do for the Western.


486
00:35:03.312 --> 00:35:06.189
Put the sex and guts and blood
up there on the screen.


487
00:35:06.357 --> 00:35:08.358
- Have you seen my cigarettes?
- Don't mind us.


488
00:35:08.526 --> 00:35:11.945
New York cut steak, 12 peas,
bottle of milk with the cap on.


489
00:35:12.113 --> 00:35:15.365
- You can't afford your own cigarettes?
- Jack has all my money.


490
00:35:15.533 --> 00:35:19.828
I hope your food isn't getting cold
at your table somewhere or something.


491
00:35:19.996 --> 00:35:22.289
No, no. We're here all night.
Don't worry.


492
00:35:22.456 --> 00:35:28.003
Now, Howard. Now, Howard. If you're
seriously talking about putting carnality ...


493
00:35:28.170 --> 00:35:32.841
... back on the silver screen, you must swear
to let me in on the casting session.


494
00:35:35.970 --> 00:35:40.849
- I have an eye for talent. Isn't that right?
- You ought to give up prancing in tights ...


495
00:35:41.017 --> 00:35:44.602
... be a talent scout.
- That prancing paid for my new yacht.


496
00:35:44.770 --> 00:35:48.231
You must all come sailing with me.
Catalina. What do you say?


497
00:35:48.399 --> 00:35:51.568
- Catalina. Sounds grand. Yeah.
- I've even managed to coax ...


498
00:35:51.736 --> 00:35:55.613
... the luscious Miss De Havilland
and her equally luscious sister to come.


499
00:35:55.781 --> 00:36:00.660
Though I fear their mother will insist on
coming, to preserve their questionable virtue.


500
00:36:00.828 --> 00:36:05.040
We shall assault these twin monuments
of pristine Britannic beauty nonetheless.


501
00:36:05.207 --> 00:36:07.250
- What do you say, Howard?
- Yeah?


502
00:36:07.668 --> 00:36:09.836
- Yeah. Yeah.
- Yeah?


503
00:36:14.133 --> 00:36:15.425
I gotta go.

504
00:36:16.302 --> 00:36:19.846
If you'll excuse us, we have --
We have to be somewhere.


505
00:36:20.181 --> 00:36:22.640
You are somewhere, Howard,
you madman.


506
00:36:22.808 --> 00:36:25.852
- Somewhere else. Excuse us.
- Charmed, gentlemen.


507
00:36:26.020 --> 00:36:29.647
Do help yourself to the poached pears.
I hear they're divine.


508
00:36:30.274 --> 00:36:33.068
Well. Howard Hughes,
ladies and gentlemen.


509
00:36:33.944 --> 00:36:35.278
Was that meant for me?

510
00:36:35.446 --> 00:36:38.782
My hero. God, all that
Hollywood talk bores me silly.


511
00:36:38.949 --> 00:36:41.951
As if there aren't more important things,
like Mussolini.


512
00:36:42.119 --> 00:36:46.039
- Where are we going, by the way?
- Do you feel like a little adventure?


513
00:36:46.207 --> 00:36:48.124
Do your worst, Mr. Hughes.

514
00:36:48.292 --> 00:36:52.504
- Think you own this place, you limey bastard?
- I'm a Tasmanian bastard, you prick.


515
00:36:52.671 --> 00:36:55.090
- Thataway, Errol.
- Let me at him!


516
00:37:28.666 --> 00:37:31.376
That's Mr. Mayer's house right there.

517
00:37:31.544 --> 00:37:33.461
Do you know where Jack Warner lives?

518
00:37:42.721 --> 00:37:46.516
- What's that on the steering wheel?
- Cellophane.


519
00:37:46.684 --> 00:37:50.562
If you had any idea of the crap
that people carry around on their hands.


520
00:37:51.105 --> 00:37:52.730
What kind of crap?

521
00:37:53.441 --> 00:37:55.108
You don't wanna know.

522
00:38:00.364 --> 00:38:02.323
Hold on to the wheel for a bit.

523
00:38:10.374 --> 00:38:13.543
That's too hard. Relax your hand.
Relax your hand.


524
00:38:19.216 --> 00:38:24.179
You see, you gotta feel the vibration
of the engine through your fingertips.


525
00:38:24.346 --> 00:38:27.390
- Do you feel that?
- Yes.


526
00:38:30.019 --> 00:38:31.686
Well, that's good.

527
00:38:32.313 --> 00:38:34.022
Golly!

528
00:38:38.402 --> 00:38:40.236
Well, she's all yours.

529
00:38:40.446 --> 00:38:44.115
- Where are you going?!
- I think there's some milk back here.


530
00:38:45.117 --> 00:38:47.911
- You just keep us steady, now.
- All right.


531
00:39:06.931 --> 00:39:08.765
- Howard.
- Yeah?


532
00:39:08.933 --> 00:39:11.893
There's a rather alarming mountain
heading our way.


533
00:39:12.061 --> 00:39:14.270
Pull back on the wheel a smidge.
Go on.


534
00:39:19.109 --> 00:39:21.694
Golly!

535
00:39:27.243 --> 00:39:32.413
I don't think I've ever met someone
who actually uses the word "golly."


536
00:39:39.630 --> 00:39:42.131
You all right?
Do you want me to take over?


537
00:39:42.299 --> 00:39:44.300
Just when I'm getting the hang of it?

538
00:39:49.640 --> 00:39:53.351
- You want some milk?
- Oh, please.


539
00:40:15.291 --> 00:40:17.500
Utterly smashing!
We'll do it again.


540
00:40:17.668 --> 00:40:20.837
I'm free Wednesday.
It's a little early for golf, though.


541
00:40:21.005 --> 00:40:23.298
Oh, no, no. I live right there.

542
00:40:23.799 --> 00:40:26.342
- Feel like a drink?
- Lead on.


543
00:40:27.553 --> 00:40:30.763
Now, that makes
for a challenging par four.


544
00:40:31.015 --> 00:40:34.684
My decorator
picked out the wallpaper and such.


545
00:40:35.352 --> 00:40:37.395
He's queer as a bedbug.

546
00:40:37.563 --> 00:40:40.315
But I just hate this room.

547
00:40:40.608 --> 00:40:42.442
Gives me the willies.

548
00:40:42.943 --> 00:40:47.030
Like I'm about to be swallowed up
by the latest issue of Town & Country.


549
00:40:55.706 --> 00:40:57.457
What room do you like?

550
00:40:58.709 --> 00:41:00.209
My study.

551
00:41:02.588 --> 00:41:04.255
Take me there.

552
00:41:20.606 --> 00:41:23.650
You are the tallest woman I know.

553
00:41:24.568 --> 00:41:28.696
And all sharp elbows and knees.
Beware.


554
00:41:51.220 --> 00:41:54.263
Will you fly me to work tomorrow?

555
00:41:56.892 --> 00:41:59.102
It is tomorrow.

556
00:42:51.864 --> 00:42:55.658
Keep your eye on the fuel. She's got
a minimum to keep her weight down.


557
00:42:55.826 --> 00:42:58.828
Two runs. That's it.
After that, you're flying on vapors.


558
00:42:58.996 --> 00:43:01.789
And then you crash and you die.
Give her easy flying.


559
00:43:01.957 --> 00:43:05.251
Don't worry about speed
and don't think about the record today.


560
00:43:05.419 --> 00:43:08.880
I wish you'd let someone else take her.
You've got 20 test pilots.


561
00:43:09.047 --> 00:43:13.384
Hell, why should I let someone else
have all the fun? See you in a bit.


562
00:43:34.364 --> 00:43:36.115
Contact!

563
00:45:05.747 --> 00:45:06.956
339.

564
00:45:09.084 --> 00:45:10.960
Goddamn!

565
00:45:32.649 --> 00:45:34.191
347.

566
00:45:35.652 --> 00:45:36.944
Son of a bitch!

567
00:46:09.311 --> 00:46:11.854
- 352.
- 352!


568
00:46:13.106 --> 00:46:14.357
Good girl.

569
00:46:24.117 --> 00:46:25.826
Damn it!

570
00:46:29.623 --> 00:46:31.749
Goddamn it!

571
00:46:32.209 --> 00:46:34.418
- Oh, God!
- There goes our meal ticket.


572
00:46:34.586 --> 00:46:36.087
Come on!

573
00:47:16.253 --> 00:47:17.670
Howard!

574
00:47:17.838 --> 00:47:20.006
- Howard!
- How did we do?


575
00:47:21.091 --> 00:47:23.426
352 on the last run.

576
00:47:25.220 --> 00:47:26.846
She'll go faster.

577
00:47:27.431 --> 00:47:29.056
Country mouse!

578
00:47:29.808 --> 00:47:33.227
- Kate! Katie!
- Upstairs, city mouse.


579
00:47:36.314 --> 00:47:39.233
Hello.
Good Lord, what happened to you?


580
00:47:39.401 --> 00:47:41.610
Oh, nothing. A hard landing.
I cut my foot.


581
00:47:41.778 --> 00:47:44.822
Sit down. I'll take care of it.
You tell me everything.


582
00:47:44.990 --> 00:47:48.826
You cannot imagine what it was like, Katie.
You cannot imagine the speed.


583
00:47:48.994 --> 00:47:52.163
- She was like a winged bullet up there.
- What did she make?


584
00:47:52.330 --> 00:47:56.500
Oh, around 352.

585
00:48:03.467 --> 00:48:04.967
You did it!

586
00:48:06.303 --> 00:48:08.137
Fastest man on the planet.

587
00:48:08.305 --> 00:48:11.557
Hot dog! I'm so proud of you.

588
00:48:11.725 --> 00:48:13.726
- She did it, baby.
- You knew she would.


589
00:48:13.894 --> 00:48:16.854
Oh, she was fine. 
She was just fine.

590
00:48:18.065 --> 00:48:19.648
Now let me see your foot.

591
00:48:19.858 --> 00:48:21.150
Yeah.

592
00:48:21.860 --> 00:48:25.446
- Good God! You're covered in blood.
- Oh, no. That's just beet juice.


593
00:48:25.614 --> 00:48:27.782
- I crashed into a beet field.
- What?


594
00:48:27.949 --> 00:48:30.159
Yeah, I crashed in a beet field.

595
00:48:33.330 --> 00:48:35.456
Let me get you cleaned up.

596
00:48:36.458 --> 00:48:41.003
- Heavens, what is this? Electrical tape?
- Yeah. Odie just sort of slammed it on there.


597
00:48:42.005 --> 00:48:47.051
But all I could think about
was getting home to see you.


598
00:48:51.765 --> 00:48:54.642
I am so proud of you.

599
00:48:59.189 --> 00:49:01.524
Now, this is gonna sting a little bit.

600
00:49:01.691 --> 00:49:05.528
Oh, this is useless.
Come to the bathroom.


601
00:49:06.738 --> 00:49:09.615
- Don't get beet juice on the carpet.
- I won't, I won't.


602
00:49:09.783 --> 00:49:12.451
- Too hot!
- Don't be a baby.


603
00:49:14.121 --> 00:49:16.956
Was the press there?

604
00:49:17.874 --> 00:49:19.166
Some.

605
00:49:19.376 --> 00:49:24.505
But they're calling everyone.
Should be on the wires by now.


606
00:49:33.098 --> 00:49:34.682
What is it?

607
00:49:37.394 --> 00:49:38.978
Kate?

608
00:49:42.232 --> 00:49:45.317
I've been famous,
for better or worse ...


609
00:49:45.861 --> 00:49:47.820
... for a long time now ...

610
00:49:47.988 --> 00:49:52.324
... and I wonder if
you know what it ...

611
00:49:52.951 --> 00:49:54.743
... really means.

612
00:49:55.912 --> 00:49:59.039
Yeah. I had my fair share
of press on Hell's Angels.


613
00:49:59.791 --> 00:50:01.584
I'm used to it.

614
00:50:03.545 --> 00:50:05.254
Are you?

615
00:50:08.925 --> 00:50:10.676
Howard, we're ...

616
00:50:13.597 --> 00:50:16.056
We're not like everyone else.

617
00:50:18.059 --> 00:50:22.980
Too many acute angles.
Too many eccentricities.


618
00:50:23.773 --> 00:50:26.609
We have to be
very careful not to ...

619
00:50:27.944 --> 00:50:31.780
... let people in,
or they'll make us into freaks.


620
00:50:32.949 --> 00:50:37.536
Kate, they can't get in here.
We're safe.


621
00:50:39.247 --> 00:50:41.123
They can always get in.

622
00:50:43.293 --> 00:50:46.712
When my brother killed himself ...

623
00:50:47.881 --> 00:50:50.466
... there were photographers
at the funeral.


624
00:50:51.676 --> 00:50:53.928
There's no decency to it.

625
00:51:06.358 --> 00:51:08.442
You know, sometimes I ...

626
00:51:12.155 --> 00:51:14.323
I get these feelings, Katie.

627
00:51:19.329 --> 00:51:21.872
I get these ideas, these ...

628
00:51:24.709 --> 00:51:27.336
... crazy ideas about ...

629
00:51:29.756 --> 00:51:32.132
... things that may not ...

630
00:51:33.385 --> 00:51:36.262
Things that may not really be there.

631
00:51:36.930 --> 00:51:38.472
Yeah.

632
00:51:45.146 --> 00:51:47.898
Sometimes I truly fear that I'm ...

633
00:51:49.943 --> 00:51:51.902
... losing my mind.

634
00:51:59.494 --> 00:52:01.370
And if I did, it would ...

635
00:52:04.457 --> 00:52:06.834
It'd be like flying blind.

636
00:52:14.968 --> 00:52:16.635
You understand?

637
00:52:20.807 --> 00:52:23.600
You taught me to fly, Howard.

638
00:52:26.563 --> 00:52:28.564
I'll take the wheel.

639
00:52:44.497 --> 00:52:48.542
Smashing all records, Howard Hughes
outdoes Jules Verne's wildest dreams.


640
00:52:48.835 --> 00:52:52.087
Around the world from New York
to New York in four days.


641
00:52:52.255 --> 00:52:55.215
Even beating Wiley Post's mark
by over three days.


642
00:52:55.383 --> 00:52:58.594
New aviation history is written
when his Lockheed monoplane ...


643
00:52:58.762 --> 00:53:01.764
... returns swiftly and safely.
A daring aviator.


644
00:53:02.223 --> 00:53:04.892
A true pioneer of the world's airways.

645
00:53:05.060 --> 00:53:09.063
From New York to Paris, he cuts Lindbergh's
time in half. Then on to Moscow.


646
00:53:09.230 --> 00:53:13.776
Thirty-five hours out of New York,
he roars across Siberia's trackless wastes.


647
00:53:13.943 --> 00:53:18.614
Sixty hours out of New York, he heads
for Alaska, most hazardous hop of all.


648
00:53:18.782 --> 00:53:21.158
Continuing the terrific pace,
he comes home ...


649
00:53:21.326 --> 00:53:23.660
... bringing new laurels
to American aviation.


650
00:53:24.996 --> 00:53:28.290
Howard Hughes and his crew
may find more worlds to conquer --


651
00:53:35.090 --> 00:53:39.635
You won't believe this. It just came over the
wires. Hughes has bought control of TWA.


652
00:53:42.389 --> 00:53:45.265
I thought Mr. Hughes
was flying around the world.


653
00:53:45.475 --> 00:53:48.852
Apparently he did it while he was flying,
over the radio.


654
00:53:56.069 --> 00:53:59.363
I have heard some disquieting rumors
about Mr. Hughes.


655
00:54:00.949 --> 00:54:04.368
I'd like to know everything
there is to know about Mr. Hughes.


656
00:54:06.830 --> 00:54:09.039
I'd like you to
attend to that for me.

657
00:54:10.041 --> 00:54:11.667
Thoroughly.

658
00:54:12.252 --> 00:54:14.670
The Pantages is glittering tonight.

659
00:54:14.838 --> 00:54:17.673
- Howard!
- Right over here. This way, over to the left.


660
00:54:17.841 --> 00:54:20.509
- Mr. Hughes, how was your flight?
- Miss Hepburn!


661
00:54:20.677 --> 00:54:23.345
- When are you gonna name the day?
- Raise your head.


662
00:54:23.513 --> 00:54:25.681
What's the next movie?
Give us the scoop.


663
00:54:25.849 --> 00:54:28.517
Right here. How many more
records are you gonna set?


664
00:54:28.685 --> 00:54:32.020
Right over here. Come on.
Give us a smile. It won't kill you.


665
00:54:32.188 --> 00:54:34.064
- Howard, this way.
- Beautiful.


666
00:54:34.232 --> 00:54:36.733
Over here, over here, Mr. Hughes.

667
00:54:36.901 --> 00:54:39.361
When are you gonna fly
around the world again?


668
00:54:39.529 --> 00:54:43.532
You gonna fly with Kate next time?
Did you get lonely without her?


669
00:54:43.700 --> 00:54:47.744
- Talk to Lindbergh about your flight yet?
- Where's Linda Darnell tonight?


670
00:54:47.912 --> 00:54:51.206
- Please, Mr. Hughes.
- Right here. Right here, Mr. Hughes.


671
00:54:51.374 --> 00:54:53.876
Are you trying to be more famous
than Lindbergh?


672
00:54:54.586 --> 00:54:58.338
You know,
fame is supposed to be my turf.


673
00:55:00.550 --> 00:55:02.217
L.B.!

674
00:55:04.846 --> 00:55:08.223
If you don't get more distinguished
every time I see you.


675
00:55:08.391 --> 00:55:10.392
You look so beautiful.

676
00:55:18.193 --> 00:55:19.818
Is that true?

677
00:55:28.620 --> 00:55:30.496
Don't worry about it, Howard.

678
00:55:30.663 --> 00:55:34.333
She's just working the room.
It's her job, baby.


679
00:55:37.378 --> 00:55:41.173
Sultry Southern tigress Ava Gardner
dazzles the room tonight.


680
00:55:41.341 --> 00:55:43.592
She's the newest star
in the MGM galaxy.


681
00:55:43.760 --> 00:55:47.387
And believe you me,
she puts the "cheese" in "cheesecake."


682
00:55:49.599 --> 00:55:55.145
Well, Jane Eyre has been selling popcorn
for over a hundred years, L.B.


683
00:56:35.895 --> 00:56:40.524
Hello.

684
00:56:45.738 --> 00:56:48.615
Could you reach me a towel?

685
00:56:56.040 --> 00:56:57.791
I ...

686
00:56:58.918 --> 00:57:02.170
I really can't do that.

687
00:57:03.798 --> 00:57:05.340
I'm sorry.

688
00:57:30.158 --> 00:57:34.494
I'm an idiot. I'm a complete idiot,
and I'm sorry.


689
00:57:34.829 --> 00:57:38.415
- Forget it.
- No, no. I'm a vain, preening ass ...


690
00:57:38.583 --> 00:57:43.587
... without a single redeeming feature.
- That's not true. You have very good teeth.


691
00:57:44.088 --> 00:57:45.547
Come on.

692
00:57:46.424 --> 00:57:50.761
I've got a better idea. Take me flying.
Or better yet, I'll take you flying.


693
00:57:50.928 --> 00:57:52.679
Do your worst, Miss Hepburn.

694
00:58:01.773 --> 00:58:05.609
Don't be so squirmy. You're gonna
get on famously with Father and Mother.


695
00:58:05.777 --> 00:58:09.404
And I'm sure they'll like you too.
Once they get to know you.


696
00:58:17.747 --> 00:58:20.540
- Hello! Hello!
- Kath, hello.


697
00:58:20.708 --> 00:58:22.250
Kathy.

698
00:58:25.213 --> 00:58:28.924
- Who's that with the camera right there?
- That's my ex-husband, Ludlow.


699
00:58:29.092 --> 00:58:31.385
Father and Mother are just mad
about Luddie.


700
00:58:31.552 --> 00:58:35.889
- What the hell's he doing here?
- Oh, he's here all the time.


701
00:58:36.766 --> 00:58:38.433
